AB Visual information search is a combination of two distinct types of
   behavior. Goal-directed search behavior occurs when consumers use stored
   search routines to collect information in a deliberate manner. In
   contrast, exploratory search behavior occurs when consumers are
   confronted with multiple pieces of information but have little stored
