   family-oriented goals represents an important measure of
   self-realization and self-fulfillment. Although each individual also has
   a private or inner self (chi), it is also subject to the collective
   will. This idea is in keeping with Confucian ideals that encourage the
   individual to focus on developing internal moral constraints and
   conquering selfishness in the pursuit of social propriety. Furthermore,
